{"id": 20497, "date": "1987-03-05T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-03-05T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=20497"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T13:24:59", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-09T20:24:59", "slug": "matr-the-patti-smith-group-and-bruce-springsteen-were-gonna-have-a-real-good-time-together", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/05/matr-the-patti-smith-group-and-bruce-springsteen-were-gonna-have-a-real-good-time-together/", "title": {"rendered": "We&#8217;re Gonna Have a Real Good Time Together"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Until it was released in the autumn of 1974 on\u00a0<em>1969: The Velvet Underground Live </em>(recorded live at The Matrix in San Francisco just a few weeks before Bruce made his first appearance there), the only way you&#8217;d be familiar with &#8220;We&#8217;re Gonna Have a Real Good Time Together&#8221; is if you&#8217;d heard Lou Reed&#8217;s rave-up at one of the band&#8217;s early concerts.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_GIK7mKN5Sg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Patti Smith had heard it, though. She ran with Reed and considered him a major influence, and by 1976 she&#8217;d incorporated the song into her set lists.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2-808ATQWK8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>On the night after Thanksgiving, Patti played a gig at The Bottom Line in New York City, and Bruce not only made an appearance, he joined Patti on stage for most of the show.</p>\n<p>Among the highlights that evening: Patti&#8217;s version of &#8220;We&#8217;re Gonna Have a Real Good Time Together&#8221; with her full band, plus Bruce doing his best Professor impression on the piano.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/CBfg__G0V9E?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>To this day, that holiday evening remains the only time Bruce has ever played this Underground classic.</p>\n<p><strong>We&#8217;re Gonna Have a Real Good Time Together<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> November 26, 1976 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> November 26, 1976 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 September 9, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce joins The Patti Smith Group on piano for a rave-up cover of The Velvet Underground classic.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69798, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterin